You're testing advertising emails for a bathing suit company and you test one version of the email in February and the other in May.

People's bathing suit buying habits are different in February vs May. You are much more likely to be swimming in May then February

You open a clinic to treat anxiety and find that the people who visit show a higher rate of anxiety than the general population.

The only peole who you are sampling are patients at an anxiety clinic. You need a more diverse sample.

You launch a new ad billboard based campaign and see an increase in website visits in the first week.

You'll want to view the increase in visits within the larger trend of the year. It may not be because of the billboard neccessarily if traffic was already trending upwards.

You launch a loyalty program but see no change in visits in the first week.

It depends on the context of when the program launched, it may be during a time when people aren't active/looking for a loyalty program.
